        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 2:37PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 237 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pinecliffe, or 27 miles northwest of Denver, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northern Lakewood, Arvada, western Westminster, southwestern
Boulder, southwestern Broomfield, western Wheat Ridge, northern
Golden, Louisville, Superior, Central City, Black Hawk, Rocky
Flats, White Ranch Open Space, Eldorado Springs, Pinecliffe,
Crescent Village and Marshall.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
